Restrictions imposed on the activities of foreign  banks operating in Russia should be lifted by Wednesay of next week, the head  of Russia's Central Bank, Viktor Guerachtchenko, said Tuesday.
"Pressure has come from several countries and also from Russian commercial  banks which, in their attempt to open subsidiaries overseas, felt like they  were running against a wall," Guerachtchenko said.
The restrictions were imposed last November and were to remain in effect  until January 1996.
